The paper focuses on developing interaction techniques and visualization tools for exploring and analyzing high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in many areas of computer science. The use of scatter plots and dimensionality reduction algorithms suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the techniques' performance and user study also suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB) as related sub-categories.
